author: Luke Kerr-Dineen
title: You won't believe how this putt managed to miss
text:
You won't believe how this putt managed to miss USA Today Sports 5 hrs ago Luke Kerr-Dineen © Provided by USA Today Sports Untitled Alvaro Quiros got thoroughly unlucky at the Portugal Masters on Friday.
AdChoices About 10 feet away for birdie on the par-5 12th hole, Quiros barely missed his putt before walking up to tap in for par. He was only about a foot away but, somehow, the ball hit the back of the cup and popped back out.
It’s a seriously rotten piece of luck. He didn’t hit the ball overly hard and it rolled straight in the middle of the hole. What’s likely is that the hole itself was cut slightly incorrectly, which caused the ball to rebound back out of the hole.
